Package model

Class FlexiblePortfolio

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.FlexiblePortfolio
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFixedPortfolio, IFlexiblePortfolio
    public class FlexiblePortfolio
extends java.lang.Object
implements IFlexiblePortfolio
    The class for flexible portfolios implements the flexible portfolio interface and extends the abstractFixedPortfolio class. Some operations that are to be performed on flexible portfolios are already implemented for fixed portfolios, hence we use the concept of code reuse to efficiently reuse the implementations of the fixed portfolios.

      • calculateCostBasis

        public java.lang.Double calculateCostBasis​(java.time.LocalDate costBasisDate)
        Description copied from interface: IFixedPortfolio
        Calculate the cost basis of a portfolio on a particular date. For fixed portfolios, the date will be today's date, as the fixed portfolios cannot be modified once created we calculate the cost basis on current date or the date on which the portfolio was created. For flexible portfolio, since it has the ability to modify the portfolio, we calculate the cost basis on a particular date.
        Specified by:
        calculateCostBasis in interface IFixedPortfolio
        Parameters:
        costBasisDate - the cost basis date
        Returns:
        the double

      • calculateChartValues

        public java.util.Map<java.time.LocalDate,​java.lang.String> calculateChartValues​(int option)
        Description copied from interface: IFixedPortfolio
        Calculate chart values. Performance of a portfolio can be visualized with the help of a chart. This method calculates the values that needs to be represented in the chart. The parameter option determines whether the user wants to view the performance of a portfolio of the previous week, previous month or the previous year. option 1 would represent previous week option 2 would represent previous month option 3 would represent previous year It returns a map, which contains the date as a key and the string of stars for this date as the value. If the value on a particular date is less than the scale then we would represent it by the symbol
        Specified by:
        calculateChartValues in interface IFixedPortfolio
